mobs.d: Guarding it's bedding, which includes a cloak of elvenkind and a holy symbol of Lieru.

labels.s: Hole to surface. Unclimable without a rope and grappling hook. Trash on the floor includes a dagger and a skullcap and a pair of leather boots.
The hiding place of a powerful artifact, now sadly stolen. It's guardian remains, however.
Roof will collapse two rounds after player passes.
High Priest's room. Journal tells of going to hide in the secret room behind the tomb of Ariku.
Key to door on the floor.
Skeleton of a priest. Has a key to the south door.
Skulls of the ancestors. Some gems hidden in eye sockets.
More skulls. One is false and opens secret door.
High Priests corpse. Has key to exit room. A chest holds a shield and priests last vague notes.
For millennia the temple of Lieru was buried beneath the dark forest. Now it has been opened, and the dead stir...
Secret Door behind sarcophagus of Ariku. Can be opened with Holy symbol of Lieru.
Dead priest. Looks like he was trying to get through the gate. It can be pulled down with a successful strenght check, or the key will be with the moledog.
Secret door, only opens from the west.
Corpse of priest. Has a staff of healing.
Alcove contains statue and holy book of Lieru. Book is fragile and damaged but some of it is readable.
